```suggestion
	for (const [key, fieldSchema] of Object.entries(schema.info as Record<string, ImplicitFieldSchema>) {
	   if (!keys.includes(key)) {
	      ...
```

That avoids two copies of the key list, and the lookup of the field schema.
Then to handle implicit field schema,
```typescript
if (fieldSchema instanceof FieldSchema) {
// Only FieldSchema instances can have defaults
const defaultProvider = fieldSchema.props?.defaultProvider;
...
```

