body:
This function is a lot more readable now IMO, thank you! 

One additional suggestion - get rid of the `keys` array. All that `keys` is doing is filtering to the string keys of data, but the loop here is already filtering - it's only checking against string keys anyway (because `Object.entries` only considers string-keyed properties, and even if it did include numbers/symbols, we know that `schema.info` only has string properties too!).

Here, you can just do:

```ts
const value = (data as Record<string, InsertableContent | undefined>)[key];
if (value !== undefined) {
	setFieldValue(/*...*/)
} else {
	// default provider case
}
```

This is straightforward to read now. "For each key in my schema, does my inserted content have this key? If yes, use its value. If no, do the default."

